article.headline: Florida A&M 83, MD Eastern Shore 72
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Brian Greene had 18 points and 10 rebounds, and Florida A&M pulled away in the second half for an 83-72 victory over Maryland-Eastern Shore on Saturday. Jonathan Kelly added 14 points for the Rattlers (12-14, 8-6 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), Glen Elliott had 12 and Tony Tate scored 10. Troy Jackson scored 23 points to lead the Hawks (5-18, 2-11). Antonio McMillon added 22, and Jesse Brooks had 11. Florida A&M led 36-33 at halftime, and McMillon's layup with 18:06 remaining gave Maryland-Eastern Shore a three-point lead. The Rattlers responded with a 14-5 run, and the Hawks never got closer than four points the rest of the way. Florida A&M shot 53 percent from the field, while the Hawks shot just 38 percent.
